	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Cincinnati</placeName> <date>May 17. 1852</date>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Rev&#39;d Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I wrote you near two weeks since&#44; which<lb/> suppose you have received&#59;&#8212;since which I received your<lb/> <date><sic>may</sic></date> Occident&#44; in addition to the old list&#44; you sent to<lb/> <persName>Messrs. Hechimer </persName> &#38; <persName>Goldsmith</persName>&#44; &#38; <persName>S &#38; W Shroeder</persName>&#44; I sent them<lb/> &#38; they were returned to me&#44; you had better not send to<lb/> nay new names&#44; without they are sent for&#59; or<lb/> ordered through me&#58;&#8212;I have sold 3 Prayer Books&#59;&#8212;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mr Rosenfeldt</persName> request me to order on from you<lb/> 6 &#40;six&#41; dozen &#39;Scriptural Questions for the use of<lb/> Sunday Schools&#39; compiled by <persName>E Pike</persName>.&#8212;<lb/> and 3 &#40;three&#41; Dozen of <persName>Mr Nathan&#39;s</persName> Road to Faith&#44; if they<lb/> can be got&#44; 100 copies would be too many at present&#44;<lb/> the expense would have to be born by 2 or 3 Individuals&#44;<lb/> excepting those that are paid for&#59; <persName>Mr Rosenfeldt&#39;s</persName> con&#45;<lb/>gregation provides no Teachers&#44; &#40;<persName>Mr Kub<add>&#63;</add></persName> having withdrawn&#41;<lb/> and our Congregation being set against it&#44; by the <hi rend="underline">pious</hi><lb/> <persName>Mr Mabzu</persName>&#59; I have found your list of Debtors since<lb/> I last wrote &#38; will endeavor to make collections&#59;<lb/>  The Sunday School still contains upwards of 100 children&#59;<lb/> The Hebrew Gentlemen&#39;s Benevolent Society&#44; at their<lb/> last Election&#44; Elected <persName>Mosely Ezekiel Esq.</persName> President<lb/> <persName>Henry Mack Esq.</persName> Vice President. <persName>Isaac Hackenberg</persName> Treasr.<lb/> <persName>Henry Harris Esq.</persName> Sect.&#8212;Hebrew Ladies Benevolent Soceity<lb/> PYO</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>No 1. <persName>Mrs. Louisa Symonds</persName> Patroness&#59; <persName>Mrs. Simeon Moses</persName> VP.<lb/> <persName>Mrs. Ferdinand Milius</persName> Treasr. &#38; Mrs. <del>Ab.</del> <persName>Mrs Abm Abraham</persName>. Secy.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">The other Societies being in whole or part benefit<lb/> Societies and amongst the Germans.  I do not know<lb/> the Officers&#59; I&#39;ll endeavor to get them and send the<lb/> names on&#59; We find it very difficult to raise funds for<lb/> our new <add>Hebrew</add> from the Ultra Orthodox portion of our<lb/> Congregation&#44; &#39;tho to please them principally we<lb/> have given a considerable sum extra to have no<lb/> work on the Building on <add>Hebrew</add>.&#8212;<persName>Mr Mabzer</persName> has given<lb/> us his seat&#44; as a <hi rend="underline">gift</hi> to <hi rend="underline">build</hi> the new Synagogue<lb/> with&#44; &#40;all we shall ever get from him&#44;&#41; and he will<lb/> sit amongst the mourners &#38;c at the bottom of the<lb/> <add>Hebrew</add>&#59;&#8212;Oh&#33; Hypocrisy&#33;&#33;&#8212;If you send the Sunday School<lb/> Books&#44; please enclose them with the next Occidents.<lb/>  <persName>Messrs. Jonas Moses</persName> &#38; <persName>Miss Phillipson</persName> send their respects.</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)">Yours truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">Joseph Jonas</persName></p>
		</body>
